It's a unique shade of blue and got a dull finish but you know what you're buying and it suits my taste completely. The dupatta is also quite long. I'm 5'5 and it reaches my ankel both front and back when I take it on one shoulder. People wearing M/L can go for 38 easily.

description: The dress looked classy. Good for a wedding wear. It's a heavy dress when it comes to weight. The material is comfortable. The cloth is embroidered and so is dupptta . It's set of anarkali and dupatta only. No lower is given. When I talk about fitting the sleeves were very tight for me. I was not able to raise my hands beyond one point because of sleeves. Not just from shoulders the sleeves were tight from below elbow also. Overall it's a nice dress but I felt it's expensive.

title: Must have
description: How I wish it had sleeves. But sleeveless is still pretty. Pure cotton, bright indigo colours with a beautiful print. The fabric could have been little more bring in colours, may be it’s a old stock. But the fitting is perfect. I’m sure, the colours won’t bleed too as it’s a reputation brand biba. The embroidery is like a necklace which can be put separately over the dress. One can wear it without it too. I love the way it’s built, layers of fabric stitched together to give a it a loose airy fit from bottom. The under fabric is soft cotton. I’m totally in love with it!
